{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"tasty-suit-fiend","description":"# Wire run_eval (Inspect Task) + eval-live CI (2.5)\n\n## What\n\nReplace the `run_eval()` NotImplementedError with a thin Inspect AI Task assembly:\ndataset -> solver (task 2.2) -> generator call -> scorers (registry, task 2.1) ->\nepochs/at_least(k)/coverage/judge_alignment(kappa over gold_set) -> JUnit via to_junit.\nBehind the `eval` extra (guard_import). Then wire `.github/workflows/eval.yml`\n`eval-live` to actually run for all specs, with community-standard CI + cost rails.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `run_eval()` runs a real Inspect eval for any spec (no longer raises NotImplementedError); offline discipline functions remain the pinned logic.\n- [ ] Deterministic scorers gate; llm-judge reports; coverage + kappa applied; JUnit emitted.\n- [ ] `eval-live` triggers on workflow_dispatch + weekly schedule (job `if:` includes 'schedule'), `continue-on-error: true` (non-blocking), `concurrency: cancel-in-progress`, explicit max-concurrency + per-run case ceiling, `actions/cache` on the response-cache dir.\n- [ ] Fork-safe: live calls never run on fork PRs/Dependabot; no pull_request_target checking out fork code; spend-cap guidance documented.\n- [ ] `eval-discipline` remains the only required PR check (zero-cost).","id":"4569-8552-6c7e-4610","parent_id":"b4af-6782-0f12-4a1d","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Wire run_eval (Inspect) + eval-live CI (2.5)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782578574404870001,"uuid":"4398248a-f290-45e3-ab17-95a648fbd754"}